# Copy to `.env` for local dev. Never commit real secrets.
#
# --- Vercel (Production / Preview) ---
# Vite bakes these in at *build* time. Your hosting must provide them when `vite build` runs.
#
# 1. Vercel → your project → Settings → Environment Variables
# 2. Add each variable with the EXACT name below (including VITE_ prefix).
# 3. Check "Production" and/or "Preview" so the build that deploys gets the values.
# 4. Save, then Deployments → Redeploy (or push a new commit).
#
# Common mistakes:
# - Using WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY without the VITE_ prefix (will not appear in the app).
# - Setting variables only for "Development" in Vercel (local `vercel dev`) but not Production.
# - Forgetting to redeploy after changing env.

# Web3Forms — https://web3forms.com
VITE_WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY=

# Contentful — Content Delivery API (Settings → API keys in your space)
# https://www.contentful.com/developers/docs/references/content-delivery-api/
VITE_CONTENTFUL_SPACE_ID=
VITE_CONTENTFUL_ACCESS_TOKEN=
